{
  "stem": "14613.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I can even remember right now many songs which we studied then.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The tradition, the Jewishness, was something that we were brought up with.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And going to Jewish school, studying about Eretz Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We also had what you can call, almost-- many families in Poland-- you had this little what we call a 'pushka,' which was a little can where you donated money for Keren Kayemeth.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father also gave a room to a Jewish organization in our factory.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was called 'Hanoar Hatzioni.' So that we were brought up with the spirit of-- call it Jewishness, or et cetera.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hanoar Hatzioni was a, a-- an organization-- it was a Zionist organization, in particular, for the youth, to bring them up in the Zionist spirit.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, my father was thinking about emigrating to-- then it was Palestine, I think.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a long time before the war, he, he bought a piece of land around Haifa because he was thinking about moving the factory and establishing a factory, textile factory, in Israel.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But as I was told, later on, as we grew older, the reason we were not going to, to Palestine-- because my mother was always saying, let the kids grow up.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Let them finish the elementary school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then when we finish elementary school, she would say, let them finish the high school and, and then the lyceum.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did not attend, at that point, too many meeting.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was a little too young, except, maybe-- not in any serious way.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Particularly that I did get a lot of Jewish education, and the spirit of, in my school that we had.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We spoke about Israel and-- so that I didn't have the need so much.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
